   {:e #blake3 "9e7769dac6a25381c670e73792b40283d22fcff40fea723db772bf7501ca6907" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Insight 12 — there are not five systems, there is ONE. Ceremony and harvest urgency are not separate 'decision systems.' They are context blocks competing for token budget alongside task recommendations and coherence metrics. The ceremony_level() function and harvest_urgency_multi() function produce INFORMATION (text strings displayed to the agent). That information occupies tokens. Those tokens have an expected ΔF(S) and a cost. The acquisition function handles them. APPROACH: (1) In methodology_context_blocks (context.rs), ensure the ceremony-protocol block and the harvest-warning block carry AcquisitionScore with: impact = ceremony benefit (how much M(t) improves from following ceremony) OR urgency_multi (how much knowledge is at risk), relevance = 1.0 (always relevant to methodology), novelty = 1/sqrt(times this specific warning was shown this session), confidence = calibrated from outcomes (did showing ceremony advice improve session M(t)?), cost = token count of the block. (2) These blocks then compete naturally in the ACP projection. High-urgency harvest blocks outrank low-impact coherence blocks. Full-ceremony blocks survive when budget allows, get cut when it doesn't. (3) REMOVE ceremony_level() as a standalone decision function. The ceremony 'level' EMERGES from which methodology blocks survive the budget gate. (4) harvest_urgency_multi() remains as an INPUT to the impact factor of the harvest-warning block — it computes the expected ΔF(S) of harvesting. But it no longer drives a separate threshold check. ACCEPTANCE: (A) ceremony_level() not called as a standalone decision anywhere in the CLI. (B) Ceremony and harvest blocks carry AcquisitionScore. (C) Budget pressure naturally suppresses low-alpha methodology blocks. (D) All tests pass. (E) The 'ceremony protocol' line in braid status still appears but is now scored by alpha, not by k_eff threshold. DEPENDS-ON: UAQ-3 (all blocks must carry AcquisitionScore first). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/context.rs + methodology.rs" :op :assert}
